Mighty Mouse and Friends Holiday Special

description:
The Age of Darkness is descending upon the Grimm Universe! All hell is about to break loose as the Dark Queen prepares to wage war on Earth and the four realms of power all at once. Can Sela, Robyn, Cross, Shang and the rest of the Realm Knights stop her in time or will the Queen finally get what she wants: Power over all things.

Volume 4 of the epic Age of Darkness series is here!

Collects Grimm Fairy Tale issues #0, #99-100, Giant-Size 2014, 2014 Annual, and Realm Knights: Age of Darkness One-Shot.
name: Volume Four

volume.name: Grimm Fairy Tales presents Age of Darkness

description:
Flashback

Flashback to the Start

Yota wants to erase the past and start over, this time with the courage to declare his love to Moemi, but it's not that easy. Moemi and Takashi are both still dealing with the aftermath of the asault on Moemi. And will Ai's own feelings interfere with her efforts to help Yota?
name: Flashback

description: Archie’s a lucky guy—he’s gotten to meet the elusive Santa Claus before! How many times? We’ll help you count with this 150-page digital exclusive, where Archie and friends share the spotlight with the big man himself! Will St. Nick and our favorite famous redhead work together to bring Christmas to the world? You’d have to see it to believe it!

Archie and the gang are getting in the holiday spirit with this collection of this year's ALL-NEW Christmas stories! First, in "Secret Santa Swap", Archie is determined to be Veronica's Secret Santa. When he pulls someone else's name, he has no choice but to find out who has Veronica so he can switch with them. This leads him on a wild goose chase around school, setting off a chain-reaction of switching names! Will he ever find out who is the mystery person who picked Veronica's name? Then, in "The Christmas App," Dilton invents a handy Christmas app that’s supposed to help Archie pick out the perfect gift for Veronica—but even modern technology can’t help find something for the girl who has everything! Archie and Jughead manage to get the whole gang in on the search, but has the answer been at the tip of their fingers all along? All of that and MORE in this ALL-NEW holly, jolly collection!

volume.name: Archie Digital Comics Presents: Archie's Christmas Stocking

description: Join Betty and Veronica for the jolliest ALL-NEW Christmas stories of the year! Veronica's got quite a collection of cards -- no, not Christmas cards, credit cards! But who knew they could provide more than just a form of payment? Find out the other use of credit in "It's in the Cards." Then, Santa is reviewing his gift list and his elves are working overtime to supply him with spreadsheets regarding the behavior of kids of all ages. But something's weird in one of his Riverdale spreadsheets: Betty Cooper—naughty? Veronica Lodge—nice?? Santa’s puzzled—usually it’s the other way around! St. Nick decides to go undercover to learn what is behind the Betty and Veronica turn-around in the best possible disguise—as a shopping mall Santa! Find out what caused this merry mix-up in “Naughty or Nice?” Unwrap these stories and MORE in this collection of ALL-NEW holiday fun!

volume.name: Archie Digital Comics Presents: Betty and Veronica Christmas Spectacular

description: It all starts with a simple domestic disturbance... but when it's Bigby's old nemesis the Woodsman who has an axe to grind, things go downhill fast.
name: Chapter One

description: Wonder Woman has always trusted her mother, Queen Hippolyta. But recent events on Apokolips may force a wedge between them!
name: Dig For Fire Part 3

volume.name: Salt Water Taffy: The Seaside Adventures of Jack and Benny
Salt Water Taffy: The Seaside Adventures of Jack and Benny
Salt Water Taffy: The Seaside Adventures of Jack and Benny
Salt Water Taffy: The Seaside Adventures of Jack and Benny
Salt Water Taffy: The Seaside Adventures of Jack and Benny
Cybertronian: The Unofficial Transformers Recognition Guide

description: A picture's worth a thousand words, and there have always been top supplies of both in the ever-moving manuals of marvels and miscreants! Now, witness first-hand the series that started it all in Mark Gruenwald's original fifteen issues worth of secrets, super-powers and schematics! About the best, by the best!
name: Volume One

volume.name: Essential Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe
Wonderful wonder world: The country of clubs

description: The original encyclopedia of adventures: expanded, augmented and updated! Marvel's continuity kings continued their quest for completeness in these issues of dedicated Deluxeness! Top talent teamed to headline heroes like Captain America, Daredevil, Doctor Strange, Nick Fury, the Hulk and dozens of others! Full lineups of the Avengers, the Defenders, the Fantastic Four and more! Collects the first third of the OFFICIAL HANDBOOK OF THE MARVEL UNIVERSE - DELUXE EDITION.
name: Volume One

volume.name: Essential Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe Deluxe Edition

description: Full-blown infotainment marks the halfway point of the encyclopedia of the Marvelous - highlighting members of the Avengers and the X-Men, and most of the Fantastic Four! Iron Man! Luke Cage! The Punisher! The horrors of Hydra and the menace of the Maggia! Magneto, Mystique and more! Special Feature: mapping the mysteries of Marvel's Manhattan!
name: Volume Two

volume.name: Essential Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe Deluxe Edition

description: How many rooms in the X-Mansion? What makes web-shooters work? Find out as Spider-Man and the X-Men join forces to highlight the third volume of this Guide to the Greats! Featuring full profiles on Rogue, Shadowcat, Storm, the White Queen, Wolverine and more! The Scarlet Witch, the Silver Surfer and so many more in glorious color! The secrets of S.H.I.E.L.D.! The schematics of the Sentinels! The story of Subterranea and the wonders of Wakanda! Plus: details on more than a hundred alien races!
name: Volume Three

volume.name: Essential Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe Deluxe Edition

description: Heroes, villains, gods, demons, sorcerers, scientists, monsters, mobsters and a talking duck: More than one thousand dynamic dossiers, collected in alphabetical order for the first time across three volumes! From mutants to martial arts, street crime to space opera, espionage to other dimensions, horror to humor, the past to the future, no corner of Marvel is left untouched! Super-team rosters and histories, alien race outlines and so much more! Get to know the Universe now!
name: Volume One

volume.name: Essential Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe Master Edition

description: Heroes, villains, gods, demons, sorcerers, scientists, monsters, mobsters and a talking duck: more than one thousand dynamic dossiers, collected in alphabetical order for the first time across three volumes! From mutants to martial arts, street crime to space opera, espionage to other dimensions, horror to humor, the past to the future, no corner of Marvel is left untouched! Super-team rosters and histories, alien race outlines and so much more! Get to know the Universe now! Includes the characters/profiles in alphabetical order.

description:
Baby's Day Out

Baby's wrecking Atlantic City! While the Army tries to contain the situation, cryptozoologist Trent Headley and his assistant, Chris, are trying to make their move and capture the monster. Meanwhile, back at police headquarters, Detective Frank Welker tries to decide between helping his department or staying away from the situation so he can retire in peace.
name: Baby's Day Out

description: In this final issue of CAAATS!, Olive and Hazel suit up as superheroes one last time, take a trip to the high seas and attempt to save a dim-witted barbarian from a giant troll. And finally, we wrap things up by saying goodbye to a dear friend. It's the final curtain, but we're going out with a bang in the latest issue of CAAATS!
Jim and Karl get ambushed DEPD agents, Director Reid makes a deal with one of Jim's old enemies, and Billy and Phoebe's research into the artifact is cut short when two familiar faces appear.
The fabric of our world started to fray with the particle smashing experiment in Issue #1, now those treads begin to tie back together...

The Ranch of Riddles

In this romantic issue of Cowgirl Romances take a trip back in time to the sweaty plains of the Wild West, where women defended the house and found romance under the stars...

Jessie Hayden's heart becomes entangled in a mysterious web of the cattle kingdom called the "Ranch of Riddles". Stella Dawson, a rodeo entrepreneur, always promised to give'm their money's worth until a new flame came to the show in "Love Rode In". Miss Kitty dreamed of the day her man would return, but when it happens is it as she imagined in "Send Back My Love". A southern bell clings to her old way of life, until romance forces a change in "My Rebel Heart" plus more and vintage advertisements.

Cowgirl Romances combines country beauties, Western villains and good ol' fashioned gun fights. Join the real heroes of the homestead in battles against bandits and for the hearts of hunky cowboys.

Enjoy a nostalgic trip down memory lane with the best titles from the golden age of comics. Yojimbo Press has lovingly remastered these timeless classics with vivid color correction and image restoration.
name: The Ranch of Riddles

description:
First Impressions

Friend or Foe? Yin Xiong wakes up to find new encounters.
name: First Impressions

description:
Just Another Day at the Office

What would you do to maintain your deepest, darkest secret?

For a vampire, the answer to that question is unsurprisingly simple.
name: Just Another Day At the Office

description:
The Oneironaut

The mysterious origins of the Spook King and the Prisoner at the top of the glowing Spire is revealed. Their connections to our heroes will shock you!
name: The Oneironaut

description:
ROUND THREE! Amarosa has survived two grueling fights and now the stakes are even higher as she finds herself where she never dreamed she'd be: space! Her hands are full trying to survive and learn about herself, but it seems that everyone knows more about her then she does!

Note: The digital edition (12/10/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Frogman Returns

Frogman Returns in... Frogman Returns. This 'Darker & Grittier' sequel sees Frogman face off against The Man-Frog, a hideous creature with a taste for tit.
name: Frogman Returns

description:
Reunion

An unexpected detour...

Salia and her brother have fled their homeworld, which has been claimed by the invading Chears. They are on their way to a new world-one untouched by Chear control.

But a news broadcast about a group of rebels reveals someone from Salia's past-someone she's never met, but who changed everything.

Will Salia finally meet the woman who saved her life?
name: Reunion

description:
Zeus, Isis, and the rest of Earth's mythological gods have a destructive plan to regain humanity's worship. Will it work? Not if Jesus, Satan, and a nun named Maria have anything to say about it! (That is, if Jesus and Satan can keep their hormones under control long enough to mount an attack.)

Back-up Features:

  • Holy F*ck Origins: 994 AD
  • Holy F*ck Origins: 1958 AD

Release Dates:

  • Digital Edition - 12/10/2014
  • Print Edition - 03/04/2015
name: Perfect Anus

description: The city of St. Barrington is under siege--and its heroes are thousands of miles away without any way home.

Enter Stranger

When Pulitzer-winner Molly Sloan and her assistant Timmy Mendez stumble upon an assassination attempt in Rumania, a mysterious stranger saves their lives just in time. Turns out, the story they've been chasing is a dead-end, but could the map they've discovered lead to something bigger? Three days later, at Lord Crawford's 55th birthday party in Scotland, the world-famous mesmerist Mysterion the Magnificent unveils a terrible surprise: the Mesmogrifier. A machine designed to turn a roomful of people into mind-slaves. As Timmy falls prey to this infernal device, Molly discovers that Lord Crawford has a terrible secret himself...
name: Enter Stranger

description: The adventures of Jack Zero continue as Jack joins Buffalo Bill's Wild West show and learns the famed "cigarette act" from Annie Oakley. But it's the lovely Rose Barclay that shows him something he'll never forget.

Fredury, leader of the Mechabots, is called upon by the Dark Lord Satan himself to assemble the Princes of the Universe and orbit the flaming ice ball that is Gleise 4368. There the Princes must combat a pod of militant beings known as the Space Whales Against Musical Pornography (S.W.A.M.P.) who are determined to censor Rock-n-Roll.

Will they succeed, or will Rock be eradicated from the quadrant? Find out in this thrilling installment of MECHABOTS: Princes of The Universe.

Robots. Space. Queen. What are you waiting for?

This is the second story in our digital and print collection, KILLER QUEEN, A COMIC ANTHOLOGY inspired by the discography of Queen. Story by Jon James, with art by Kelly Williams; letters by Mark Mullaney. This story also features Queen-inspired vignettes from artist CGhirardo, including "I Want Out" and "One Vision".
name: Mechabots The Princes of the Universe

description: Prepare to behold one of the greatest sagas in the annals of Asgard when the Mighty Thor teams up with Hercules! It's page after page of boasts, battles and broken bones as the two titans fight their way into Pluto's underworld to save the lovely Krista! And that's not all we have in store for you: Thor, Sif and Balder's journey across the cosmos to stop the mysterious Black Stars from destroying the Rigellian homeworld; the unstoppable Destroyer returns; Galactus' herald Firelord makes his debut; and the origin of Ego the Living Planet is revealed! With scripts by Gerry Conway and art by the incomparable John Buscema, there's no doubt they're Marvel Masterworks of the highest order! Collecting THOR (1966) #217-228 and MARVEL TREASURY EDITION #3.
name: Volume 13

description: Mercy and Wallace are patting themselves on the back believing that they have rid the house of all the supernatural pests. But, a mysterious man who looks a lot like Mr. Rhee warns them they haven't finished the job.

Morgan's learning that there are some definite upsides to being a teen-aged super-type -- like riding the original winged horse, PEGASUS! Unfortunately, the downsides include stuff like a mundane museum field trip turning deadly when the savage she-spider ARACHNE comes to call! Guest-starring THE ODYSSEY's super-strong SIGMA!
TOP SECRET: A case for Lt. Snugglesworth PLUS: Silver fish of the silver screen!

The crew of the Skybreaker met with General Clopas' troops and did not fare well, to say the least. One shot, maybe killed. Two captured. And one coerced into helping the enemy. But they do still have that coin and compass, right? Where will it lead, and to what?

Beware The Beastman

Prehistoric Sci-Fi Fantasy Adventure.
name: Beware The Beastman

description:
Torture, Chaos, Dinner!

Chaos Lords, Zoltakk and Phil, have conquered the city of Spirekassle, but their plans don't stop there. Enlisting the help of Pewfell, Bish and a 10 foot pole they plan to mount an expedition into the deepest, most ancient dungeons beneath the city to recover a long-lost magical artifact of limitless power.
name: Torture, Chaos, Dinner!

description: Continuing PROPHET HILL illustrated by Oliveira, HUGO BROYLER illustrated by Paronzini, VIVID illustrated by Oliveira, and featuring BATTLE GODS 2 by F.Ruiz Velasco and THE WRONG HERO illustrated by Paronzini.

From tears to soda fountains, from mobsters to pretty ingénues in freshly pressed dresses, the stories of love and betrayal herein will prompt you to grab a tissue box or swoon in delight. Featuring two of Joe Simon and Jack Kirby's sensational romance comics, "If You Want Me" focuses on a construction worker with a silver tongue who cannot abide the live of a lowly writer. Meanwhile, "The Town and Toni Benson" follows a newly wed couple trying to make the most of life in a town that doesn't want them within the city limits. Cup your lover's face and pull them in for a sweet kiss or crack open this book for an even BETTER time.

Meet New Zealand's new action hero... with feathers!

In the North Island of New Zealand, there is a place called Whale Bay. It is here, a little brown kiwi calls home. Kory and his friend Bert the green gecko, enjoy surfing and fishing. Adventure tracks these two characters and they find themselves face to face with danger on their way to rescue Kory's family. Can Kory outwit a dangerous wolf and get himself and his family out of trouble?

One rescue. One escape. One flight that will ruffle your feathers!

volume.name: The Adventures of Kory: Flight of the Kiwi

description:
Rough Landings

Welcome to Antispire

You are about to embark on an epic journey into a realm of magic and mystery. Into the realm of Antispire...

Antispire, a city, a country, an alliance of races but above all, Antispire is an ideal. An ideal that by working together, nothing is impossible. Unfortunately that ideal has been shattered and Antispire has fallen. Now the dead hunt the living and nowhere is safe.

Now the fate of Antispire rests on the shoulders of a nobody from our world. Heaven help us all..
name: Rough Landings

description: Masked Mexican wrestler Aski makes his comic book debut! What adventures await the Mayan Warrior in the jungles of Yucatan?

volume.name: Aski - Rumble in the Lost Temple

description:
Mogwui Mayhem

B-Squad is sent to a strange cancer research facility which is attempting to use a limited supply of endangered and highly inbred "mogwui" creatures to cure cancer in children. B-Squad is sent in to attempt to protect the population of free-range mogwui from a mysterious group of poachers.
name: Mogwui Mayhem

description: Sr. Francesca is an Argentine nun from the Franciscan Sisters of the Precious Blood. She has resided in the United States for the past six years working primarily with teens in the slums of Amboy, New Jersey. She is known and loved by all for her compassionate heart, understanding, and especially for her fantasy filled stories surrounding the border between Mexico and the United States. She hopes to express to her teens the damage sinful patterns cause in their lives and the need for daily conversion.
name: The Stories of Sr. Francesca Huerta, FSPB

description: Michael Zigerlig's stunning vision of H.P. Lovecraft's classic tale is here!

Ruerune, a high school boy with the ability to sense alien creatures, and Pi, a girl science geek, set up an "X-file"-ish club to help the inhabitants of an alien world. A wonderful work from Singapore's acclaimed manga artist FSc!!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter #1: RueRune
  • Chapter #2: Specimen Secured
  • Chapter #3: Subject Background
  • Chapter #4: Experiment Expanded
  • Chapter #5: next Move
  • Chapter #6: Transplant
  • Chapter #7: Hosts
  • Chapter #8: Clairvoyance
name: Vol. 1

description:
Rihito Sajou, a hyperventilating overachiever, winds up attending a high school where the only requirement for graduation is knowing how to write you name. Due to some extenuating circumstances, he is now being tutored by one of the many school idiots, Hikaru "Beyan" Kusakabe. For two students who had never before had a real conversation, what does the future hold now that they are constantly together? Follow these boys as they experience excitement, betrayal, depression, and love; that unyielding, crazy, poignant, and fantastical kind of love.

Contents

  • Summer
  • Autumn
  • His First
  • A Complex Fool and a Simple Fool
  • The Second Summer
name: Vol. 1

description:
Welcome to My Nightmare

In 2029 in the Basement of Corporatica, slugs a lowly waste disposal supervisor, MiG. Under the ever-present watchful eye of WHYSOC, the Iraq War veteran struggles to survive. Now, we find him struggling to survive as he begins losing his long-standing fight with PTSD and all his old nightmares have come back to life.
name: Welcome To My Nightmare

description:
One-Shot

This Graphic Novel is a fresh take on the zombie genre. Imagine if your town was over-run by klowns-not any kind of klowns-but Zombie-Klowns. As you run screaming from these Flesh-Eating-Painted-Faced-Freaks, how will you survive? Welcome to the world of DEAD KLOWNS.

Comic book veteran Shon C. Bury and U.S. Army veteran Scott Mccullough team up as the creator/writer team for Doorkickers. With amazing and gritty art by Douglas Franchin and Michele Nucera, the Doorkickers come to life in this prologue issue.

The Doorkickers are an elite team from the Enhanced Services Directorate, a secret government organization that researches and fights the paranormal and supernatural. They're SEAL Team 6 if SEAL Team 6 fought Lovecraftian horrors. This issue hits the ground running and doesn't hold back on spectral-charged Reaver Rounds when it comes to fighting extra-dimensional entities!

Optimized for mobile devices, this Doorkickers issue has 20 story pages and a bonus memo to shed some light into the world of the ESD.
